                <p>Welcome to the tranquil neighbourhood of Cambrian Heights, set amid lush rolling landscapes in Calgary's northwest corridor and offering residents spectacular city views. </p>
                <p>John Laurie Boulevard and 40th Avenue border the community's north side, while Northmount Drive and Cambrian Drive form the neighbourhood's southern border. On the eastern edge lies 9th Street and 10th Street, while 14th Street borders the community's western edge.</p>
                <p>There's a home here for everyone in Cambrian Heights – no matter their budget. You can have your pick from large family bungalows with sprawling backyards, modern apartments, and even smaller houses.</p>
                <p>Cambrian Heights is a much sought-after neighbourhood for several reasons. It's affordable, offers a variety of housing, and is a self-sufficient community. Cambrian Heights is close to some of Calgary's best parks that offer families a wide variety of things to do for all age groups, including biking and hiking trails, picnic spots, and more. The Calgary Winter Club is just a few steps away for fitness enthusiasts. The neighbourhood is also a stone's throw away from some of Calgary's finest malls.</p>
