        <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Demographics</h3>
            <p>In 2016, there were 2,265 living in Cambrian Heights (2016 Census of Canada). A large population of children and seniors (almost 30%) lives in the community. Owners occupy about 60% of the houses and the rest are rented out.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Housing</h3>
            <p>Dwellings in Cambrian Heights consist of large, mid-century bungalows with large open yards. Most houses here were built in the 1950s. Many of these houses have been renovated and fitted with modern fixtures. There are newer homes and apartments too. While many of the homes are single detached houses, you will find several duplexes, row houses, and apartments here.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Developer/builder/history</h3>
            <p>Cambrian Heights was annexed to the city of Calgary in 1910, but it was only years later (1957) that real estate developed here. Today, this is a well-established community with almost a thousand private households.</p>
        </div>
