        <h2>FAQs about Cambrian Heights Real Estate and Neighborhood</h2>
        <ol>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
                <h3>Which is the nearest restaurant?</h3>
                <p>When you live in Cambrian Heights, you must try Puspa Restaurant on 40th Avenue NW, known for its creamy butter chicken and cashmere chicken. The restaurant has received some fantastic reviews for its consistently excellent food and friendly service. Cambrian Heights also boasts a variety of restaurants, fast food places and pubs so you can be sure to find an amazing meal to satisfy any craving.</p>
            </li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
                <h3>How do I get around the city?</h3>
                <p>Residents have access to several transport options. There is public transport available to get you to any part of the city. A few bus lines run through the neighbourhood, with several bus stops located at strategic locations. Cambrian Heights is a relatively walkable neighbourhood, and you can complete most of your errands on foot.</p>
            </li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
                <h3>Will I feel safe in Cambrian Heights? What is the crime like?</h3>
                <p>Cambrian Heights is safer than 76% of Alberta cities. Crime here is 12% lower than the national average, and violent crimes are 31% lower than the national average. The nearest police facility is District 3 Office (North Haven) and a three-minute drive away, giving residents a sense of safety and peace of mind. The nearest fire station (Fire Station 7) is less than two kilometres away.</p>
            </li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
                <h3>Is daycare available in the neighbourhood?</h3>
                <p>Yes, Children Come First has an Out-of-School Care Program for children ages 5 to 12 at all locations (including Cambrian Heights School).</p>
                <p>The Calgary Kids Center is located on Northmount Drive and offers out-of-school child care for kindergarten-aged children up to 12 years of age. Here children will be encouraged to continue learning new skills and languages while also receiving guidance on homework and other after-school activities.</p>
                <p>Happy Souls Playschool on 14th Street NW provides excellent before-and-after care. The staff is warm, friendly, communicative, and, more importantly – parents and children are delighted with the care provided here.</p>
            </li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
                <h3>Which is the closest hospital?</h3>
                <p>Foothills Medical Centre – one of Calgary's largest hospitals and the largest hospital in Alberta, is less than four kilometres from Cambrian Heights. Foothills Medical Centre is a full-fledged, fully-equipped hospital with over 1,100 beds.</p>
            </li>
        </ol>
